3. Difference Between Declarative & Scripted Pipelines in Jenkins?

EXPLAIN IN THIS ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Declarative Pipelines are structured, easy to maintain, and recommended for most CI/CD workflows. 
ğŸ‘‰ Scripted Pipelines offer more flexibility but require deeper Groovy knowledge. 
âœ… I prefer Declarative Pipelines for readability, but I use Scripted Pipelines when I need advanced logic and dynamic behavior.

1ï¸âƒ£ Scripted Pipeline (Groovy-Based, Code-Driven Pipeline)
ğŸ‘‰ Written in Groovy inside a Jenkinsfile.
ğŸ‘‰ Provides full control over pipeline logic.
ğŸ‘‰ Supports complex logic, loops, and conditional execution.
ğŸ’¡ Example Scripted Pipeline:
node {
    stage('Build') {
        sh 'mvn clean package'
    }
    stage('Test') {
        sh 'mvn test'
    }
    stage('Deploy') {
        sh 'kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml'
    }
}

2ï¸âƒ£ Declarative Pipeline (YAML-Style, Structured Pipeline)
ğŸ‘‰ A structured, readable pipeline syntax using pipeline {} blocks.
ğŸ‘‰ Easier to maintain than scripted pipelines.
ğŸ‘‰ Recommended for most CI/CD use cases.
ğŸ’¡ Example Declarative Pipeline:
pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean package'
            }
        }
        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn test'
            }
        }
        stage('Deploy') {
            steps {
                sh 'kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml'
            }
        }
    }
}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4.  What is "Pipeline as Code" in Jenkins?

EXPLAIN IN THIS ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ "Pipeline as Code means defining Jenkins pipelines using 
  a version-controlled Jenkinsfile instead of manually configuring jobs in the UI.
  This approach ensures automation, consistency, and collaboration in CI/CD workflows." 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5. What is a Jenkinsfile & How is it Used?

EXPLAIN IN THIS ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ "A Jenkinsfile is a version-controlled script that defines a Jenkins pipeline in code. 
  It allows CI/CD automation by defining build, test, and deployment stages inside a Git repository."


















